ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN RealCID COMMENT 'Real (funded) customer ID - HASH distribution key; primary join key shared with DDR daily/customer analytics. **Not pre-filtered** to valid-only users - add `WHERE IsValidCustomer_<Period> = 1` when aligning to standard retail analytics semantics from `DWH_dbo.Fact_SnapshotCustomer` section 2.2 (Popular Investors qualify when section 2.2 yields 1). (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN Date COMMENT 'Reporting `(date)` = procedure parameter `@date` on `BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status`; written once per rollup batch. (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN DateID COMMENT 'Reporting `(int yyyymmdd)` = `@dateInt = CAST(CONVERT(varchar(8), @date, 112) AS INT)` ; delete/reinsert key (`DELETE WHERE DateID = @dateID`). (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN FirstActionType_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`FirstActionType`. `First trading action type` wording from DDR daily wiki (Function population). `''NoAction''` sentinel behavior identical to daily. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status); periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN RegulationID_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`RegulationID`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: Customer''s assigned regulatory jurisdiction. DEFAULT 0. Sourced from Ext_FSC_BackOffice_RegulationChangeLog.ToRegulationID - end-of-day change. See Fact section 2.4. FK to Dim_Regulation. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. **Origin tier/tag:** `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
