ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN IsFunded_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`IsFunded`. Rolling funded flag **`IsFunded`** from daily table (Guy M change 2025-11-20: **evaluate on LAST day within the rolling window**, not merely any intra-period day). Implemented as inner `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN IsFunded END)` so it mirrors the **`@date` daily row** conditioned on still being inside the labeled period. Matches UC annotation on `main.bi_db.*` periodic export. Meaning roots in daily `Function_Population_Funded` documentation. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Funded); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN FirstTimeFunded_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`FirstTimeFunded`. Counts how many intra-period days flagged `FirstTimeFunded`; because `FirstFundedDateID` is immutable, observed DISTINCT values collapse to **`0`** or **`1`** but storage type remains `SUM` output (integer  >= 0). Logic identical to DDR daily wiki `FirstTimeFunded` row. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_First_Time_Funded); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status)/(Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN ActiveTraded_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`ActiveTraded`. **Sum of intra-period DDR active-trade days.** Each daily `ActiveTraded` obeys `Function_Population_Active_Traders` rules enumerated in DDR daily wiki section 2.4 (explicit ActionType/OpenMirror qualifiers). Interpret `> 0` as “had  >= 1 qualifying active day”; not a plain 0/1 mask. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Active_Traders); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status)/(Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN Portfolio_Only_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`Portfolio_Only`. Counts distinct daily rows satisfying `Portfolio_Only > 0 AND ActiveTraded = 0` inside the rolling window - implements DDR hierarchy (active traders suppressed). Mirrors daily `Portfolio_Only` definition (HODL / open TP or Options holdings without intra-day qualifying trading actions). (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Portfolio_Only); rollup mechanics (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN BalanceOnlyAccount_ThisWeek COMMENT 'Rolling `Week` slice `DateID BETWEEN @weekstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@weekstart DATE = DATEADD(week, DATEDIFF(ww, 0, @date), -1)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`BalanceOnlyAccount`. Counts daily rows satisfying `BalanceOnlyAccount > 0 AND ActiveTraded = 0 AND Portfolio_Only = 0` - cash-at-eToro tier per `Function_Population_Balance_Only_Accounts` (DDR daily section 2.4). (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Balance_Only_Accounts); rollup mechanics (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
