ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN FirstActionType_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`FirstActionType`. `First trading action type` wording from DDR daily wiki (Function population). `''NoAction''` sentinel behavior identical to daily. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status); periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN RegulationID_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`RegulationID`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: Customer''s assigned regulatory jurisdiction. DEFAULT 0. Sourced from Ext_FSC_BackOffice_RegulationChangeLog.ToRegulationID - end-of-day change. See Fact section 2.4. FK to Dim_Regulation. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. **Origin tier/tag:** `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN IsCreditReportValidCB_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`IsCreditReportValidCB`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: **1 if customer is eligible for CreditBureau credit report validation (CB = CreditBureau context).** ETL-computed CASE on PlayerLevelID, AccountTypeID, LabelID, CountryID - see Fact section 2.3. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. Origin `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN IsValidCustomer_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`IsValidCustomer`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: **1 if the customer is a valid retail customer for analytics purposes. ETL-computed from PlayerLevelID, LabelID, CountryID.** See Fact section 2.2 (explicit CASE list). DDR codebase surfaces this flag as **`IsValidCustomer_*`, not `IsValidUser`** - apply whichever column name exists on the joined object. **Regulatory/regulated subsets still align to `IsCreditReportValidCB_*`** separately. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate ...';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN MifidCategorizationID_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`MifidCategorizationID`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: MiFID II client categorization (Retail/Professional/Eligible Counterparty). DEFAULT 0. Source: Ext_FSC_BackOffice_Customer.MifidCategorizationID (BO). FK to Dim_MifidCategorization. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN PlayerLevelID_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`PlayerLevelID`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: Account tier: 4=demo, other values=real tiers. DEFAULT 0. Source: Ext_FSC_Real_Customer_Customer.PlayerLevelID (CC). FK to Dim_PlayerLevel. Critical field for interpreting `IsValidCustomer`. Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN CountryID_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`CountryID`. Verbatim Snapshot meaning: Customer''s registered country. DEFAULT 0. Source: Ext_FSC_Real_Customer_Customer.CountryID (CC). FK to Dim_Country (daily wiki notes CountryID filters for segmentation). Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. Relayed Snapshot column `(Tier 2 - DWH_dbo.SP_Fact_SnapshotCustomer)`. Periodic reshape (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN MarketingRegion_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`MarketingRegion`. Marketing geography label from DDR daily wiki (`Dim_Country.MarketingRegionManualName` lineage). Inner `ACTIVETYPEPREP`: for static snapshot attributes SP uses `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN column END)` where `rn=1` is `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY RealCID ORDER BY DateID DESC)` within `DateID BETWEEN @yearstartInt AND @dateInt` - i.e., the **`@date`** daily slice. Outer insert applies `SUM(..)`/`GROUP BY` but each customer/date collapses to a scalar duplicate of that daily value. (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN IsFunded_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`IsFunded`. Rolling funded flag **`IsFunded`** from daily table (Guy M change 2025-11-20: **evaluate on LAST day within the rolling window**, not merely any intra-period day). Implemented as inner `MAX(CASE WHEN <window> AND rn=1 THEN IsFunded END)` so it mirrors the **`@date` daily row** conditioned on still being inside the labeled period. Matches UC annotation on `main.bi_db.*` periodic export. Meaning roots in daily `Function_Population_Funded` documentation. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Funded); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN FirstTimeFunded_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`FirstTimeFunded`. Counts how many intra-period days flagged `FirstTimeFunded`; because `FirstFundedDateID` is immutable, observed DISTINCT values collapse to **`0`** or **`1`** but storage type remains `SUM` output (integer  >= 0). Logic identical to DDR daily wiki `FirstTimeFunded` row. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_First_Time_Funded); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status)/(Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN ActiveTraded_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`ActiveTraded`. **Sum of intra-period DDR active-trade days.** Each daily `ActiveTraded` obeys `Function_Population_Active_Traders` rules enumerated in DDR daily wiki section 2.4 (explicit ActionType/OpenMirror qualifiers). Interpret `> 0` as “had  >= 1 qualifying active day”; not a plain 0/1 mask. (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Active_Traders); rollup (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status)/(Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN Portfolio_Only_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`Portfolio_Only`. Counts distinct daily rows satisfying `Portfolio_Only > 0 AND ActiveTraded = 0` inside the rolling window - implements DDR hierarchy (active traders suppressed). Mirrors daily `Portfolio_Only` definition (HODL / open TP or Options holdings without intra-day qualifying trading actions). (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Portfolio_Only); rollup mechanics (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
ALTER TABLE main.bi_db.gold_sql_dp_prod_we_bi_db_dbo_bi_db_ddr_customer_periodic_status ALTER COLUMN BalanceOnlyAccount_ThisQuarter COMMENT 'Rolling `Quarter` slice `DateID BETWEEN @quarterstartInt AND @dateInt` (with `@quarterstart date = DATEADD(qq, DATEDIFF(qq, 0, @date), 0)`): pulls from sibling `BI_DB_dbo.BI_DB_DDR_Customer_Daily_Status`.`BalanceOnlyAccount`. Counts daily rows satisfying `BalanceOnlyAccount > 0 AND ActiveTraded = 0 AND Portfolio_Only = 0` - cash-at-eToro tier per `Function_Population_Balance_Only_Accounts` (DDR daily section 2.4). (Tier 1 - Function_Population_Balance_Only_Accounts); rollup mechanics (Tier 2 - BI_DB_dbo.SP_DDR_Customer_Periodic_Status)';
